ing plan:\\n\\n# Plan: `entire trail` command\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nPR #738 in entire.io introduces a \\\"Trails\\\" system on the web — a branch-centric work tracking abstraction stored on an `entire/trails` orphan branch. Trails answer \\\"why/what\\\" (human intent) while Checkpoints answer \\\"how/when\\\" (machine snapshots). They're linked by branch name.\\n\\nThis plan adds the CLI counterpart: an `entire trail` command that creates and manages trail metadata locally in git. When pushed (via pre-push hook), the web UI picks it up via webhooks automatically. Additionally, trails are auto-created when an agent session starts on a non-main branch.\\n\\n## Command Structure\\n\\n```\\nentire trail              # Show current branch's trail (or list if none)\\nentire trail list          # List all trails (with optional --status filter)\\nentire trail create        # Create a trail for current or new branch\\nentire trail update        # Update trail metadata (status, title, etc.)\\n```\\n\\n## Key Design Decisions\\n\\n- **Storage**: Dedicated `entire/trails` orphan branch (matches web PR)\\n- **ID format**: 12 hex char IDs with `<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/` sharding (same as checkpoints)\\n- **Auto-create**: On session start (UserPromptSubmit hook), if on a non-main branch without a trail, auto-create one with status `in_progress`\\n- **Push**: Pre-push hook pushes `entire/trails` alongside `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n- **Linking**: Trail ↔ Checkpoints linked by branch name (no foreign key)\\n\\n## Data Format\\n\\n### `entire/trails` branch structure\\n```\\n<trail_id[:2]>/<trail_id[2:]>/\\n  metadata.json\\n  discussion.json    # Empty initially, comments come later\\n```\\n\\n### `metadata.json` (matches web PR format)\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"trail_id\\\": \\\"abcdef123456\\\",\\n  \\\"branch\\\": \\\"feature/auth\\\",\\n  \\\"base\\\": \\\"main\\\",\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Add user authentication\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n  \\\"author\\\": \\\"alice\\\",\\n  \\\"assignees\\\": [],\\n  \\\"labels\\\": [],\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-18T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"updated_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-20T14:22:00Z\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Trail Status Lifecycle\\n```\\ndraft → open → in_progress → in_review → done → closed\\n```\\n\\n## Implementation Steps\\n\\n### 1. Add `TrailsBranchName` constant\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/paths/paths.go` (line 38)\\n\\nAdd `TrailsBranchName = \\\"entire/trails\\\"` alongside existing `MetadataBranchName`.\\n\\n### 2. Create trail package\\n**New directory**: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/`\\n\\n#### `trail.go` — Types and helpers\\n- `TrailID` type (12 hex chars, same pattern as `checkpoint/id.CheckpointID` in `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id/id.go`)\\n  - `Generate()`, `Validate()`, `Path()`, `String()`, `IsEmpty()`\\n- `TrailStatus` type with constants: `StatusDraft`, `StatusOpen`, `StatusInProgress`, `StatusInReview`, `StatusDone`, `StatusClosed`\\n  - `ValidStatuses()` and `IsValid()` for validation\\n- `TrailMetadata` struct matching web PR format (trail_id, branch, base, title, description, status, author, assignees, labels, created_at, updated_at, merged_at)\\n- `TrailDiscussion` struct (initially `Comments []TrailComment` — empty, ready for future use)\\n- `TrailComment` and `TrailCommentReply` structs (matching web PR)\\n- `HumanizeBranchName(branch string) string` helper\\n  - Strip common prefixes (`feature/`, `fix/`, `bugfix/`, `chore/`, `hotfix/`, `release/`)\\n  - Replace `-`/`_` with spaces, capitalize first word\\n\\n#### `store.go` — Git storage operations\\n`TrailStore` wrapping `*git.Repository`:\\n- `NewTrailStore(repo)` constructor\\n- `EnsureBranch()` — create `entire/trails` orphan branch if needed\\n  - Follow pattern from `checkpoint.GitStore.ensureSessionsBranch()` (`cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1264`)\\n- `Write(ctx, metadata, discussion)` — write metadata.json + discussion.json to sharded path\\n- `Read(ctx, trailID)` — read a single trail by ID\\n- `FindByBranch(ctx, branchName)` — find trail for a branch (scan all metadata.json files)\\n- `List(ctx)` — list all trails\\n- `Update(ctx, metadata)` — update existing trail (read-modify-write)\\n- `Delete(ctx, trailID)` — remove trail from tree\\n\\nReuse exported functions from checkpoint package:\\n- `checkpoint.CreateBlobFromContent()` — `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1320`\\n- `checkpoint.BuildTreeFromEntries()` — `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go` (exported)\\n- `checkpoint.FlattenTree()` — `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go` (exported)\\n- `checkpoint.GetGitAuthorFromRepo()` — `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1457`\\n\\n### 3. Create trail command\\n**New file**: `cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go`\\n\\n#### `entire trail` (root, no subcommand)\\n- If on a branch with a trail → show trail details (title, status, branch, base, timestamps)\\n- If no trail for current branch → fall through to `entire trail list` output\\n\\n#### `entire trail list`\\n- Scan `entire/trails` branch, list all trails\\n- Flags: `--status <status>` (filter), `--json` (JSON output)\\n- Table output: branch, title, status, author, created_at\\n\\n#### `entire trail create`\\n- Interactive mode (default): prompt for title, description, base branch\\n  - Title defaults to `HumanizeBranchName(currentBranch)`\\n  - Base defaults to detected default branch — reuse `strategy.GetDefaultBranchName()` (`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:1447`)\\n  - Uses `NewAccessibleForm()` for accessibility (`cmd/entire/cli/utils.go`)\\n- Non-interactive flags: `--title`, `--description`, `--base`, `--branch`, `--status`\\n  - If `--branch` specified and branch doesn't exist, create it via `git checkout -b`\\n  - If no `--branch`, use current branch via `GetCurrentBranch()` (`cmd/entire/cli/git_operations.go:156`)\\n  - Error if on main/master — use `IsOnDefaultBranch()` (`cmd/entire/cli/git_operations.go:83`)\\n- Initial status: `StatusDraft` for explicit create, `StatusInProgress` for auto-create\\n\\n#### `entire trail update`\\n- Requires being on a branch with a trail (or `--branch` flag)\\n- Flags: `--status`, `--title`, `--description`, `--label add:X`, `--label remove:X`\\n- Updates `updated_at` timestamp automatically\\n\\n### 4. Auto-create trail on session start\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — in `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (line 112)\\n\\nInsert after session initialization (line ~145), before return:\\n1. Get current branch via `GetCurrentBranch()` (`cmd/entire/cli/git_operations.go:156`)\\n2. Check if on default branch via `IsOnDefaultBranch()` — skip if true or error\\n3. Open trail store, call `FindByBranch(ctx, branchName)`\\n4. If trail already exists, skip\\n5. If no trail, auto-create:\\n   - Trail ID: `trail.GenerateID()`\\n   - Branch: current branch name\\n   - Base: `strategy.GetDefaultBranchName(repo)` — need to open repo first\\n   - Title: `trail.HumanizeBranchName(branchName)`\\n   - Status: `trail.StatusInProgress`\\n   - Author: git user.name from `checkpoint.GetGitAuthorFromRepo()`\\n6. Write trail via store\\n7. Log: `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"[entire] Created trail for branch: %s\\\\n\\\", branchName)`\\n8. Non-blocking: wrap in helper, log errors but don't fail the session\\n\\n### 5. Push trails in pre-push hook\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go`\\n\\nAdd `PushTrailsBranch(remote string) error` function:\\n- Reuse `pushSessionsBranchCommon()` pattern (line 26) but with `paths.TrailsBranchName`\\n- Same logic: check if branch exists locally, compare with remote, push with conflict resolution\\n\\nUpdate pre-push handlers to also call `PushTrailsBranch()`:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go:12` — add after existing push\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go:120` — add after existing push\\n\\n### 6. Register trail command\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/root.go` (line 86, before help command)\\n\\nAdd `cmd.AddCommand(newTrailCmd())`.\\n\\n